description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a challenging job?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to exciting developments within the trust we are looking for an enthusiastic, hard working person to join our Occupational Therapy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Occupational Therapy department has a friendly, supportive atmosphere and a real team ethic. We know how to look after our staff - making sure they achieve the ideal work-life balance. We are therefore looking for applicants who are highly motivated and share these values, to come and work with us to provide top class patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would be responsible for the department’s equipment and stock management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will include :-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;maintenance of stock,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;use of computerised ordering and stock control systems,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;liaison with outside agencies and patients families,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;teaching patients and their families how to use and fit the equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking equipment out to patients homes and onto the wards and fitting items&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;cleaning returned equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participating in the Dept. equipment training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our broad and varied workload offers every opportunity to further your experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caroline Reynolds, Deputy Occupational Therapy Manager on 01753 633522 or caroline.reynolds@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Farieda Adams, Occupational Therapy Manager on 01753 633522 or Farieda.adams@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
